    (free, lab-based, aligned to course topics)

-   OWASP Juice Shop companion guide: pwning.owasp-juice.shop
    (self-study continuation)

**Appendix A --- VM Setup for Flask Exercises**

Run this script once per VM during provisioning to install all Flask
dependencies used across the supplement:

> #!/bin/bash
>
> \# flask_setup.sh --- run as ubuntu user on each delegate VM
>
> pip3 install \--break-system-packages \\
>
> flask \\
>
> flask-sqlalchemy \\
>
> flask-login \\
>
> flask-jwt-extended \\
>
> flask-limiter \\
>
> flask-talisman \\
>
> bcrypt \\
>
> pip-audit
>
> \# Clone the supplement app directory
>
> git clone https://github.com/YOUR_REPO/vuln_flask_app
> \~/vuln_flask_app
>
> \# Or copy from instructor VM:
>
> \# scp -r ubuntu@INSTRUCTOR_IP:\~/vuln_flask_app \~/vuln_flask_app
>
> echo \"Flask supplement ready. Run: cd \~/vuln_flask_app && flask run
> \--port 5000\"

**Appendix B --- Recommended Supplement App Structure**

A single Git repository containing one self-contained Python file per
module exercise, each runnable independently. This allows delegates to
reset to a known state between exercises.

